==English==

===Etymology===
{{OE.}} ''[[bogett]], [[bouget]]'', {{F.}} ''[[bougette]]'' bag, wallet. From the gaulic BULGA "bellow" a common root with the germanic.

===Pronunciation===
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ʌdʒɪt|-ʌdʒɪt]]

===Adjective===
'''budget'''
# of, or relating to a budget
# [[appropriate]] to a [[restricted]] budget
#:''We flew on a '''budget''' airline.''

====Translations====
* Swedish : [[budget-]] (1,2)

===Noun===
'''budget'''
# [[Amount]] of [[money]] or [[resource]]s [[earmark]]ed for a particular [[activity]] or [[time-frame]].
# An [[itemized]] [[summary]] of [[intended]] [[expenditure]]

